The paper deals with a communication network with interference and states, which is a classic problem in information theory (cs.IT). The concept of opportunistic communications is also relevant to networked systems (cs.NI) and signal processing (cs.SI). The paper also discusses power control, which is a common technique in multimedia communication (cs.MM) and communication engineering (cs.CE).
